        ## Common Patterns
        
        ### Protected Route
        ```tsx
        // app/[locale]/dashboard/layout.tsx
        import { redirect } from 'next/navigation'
        import { createServerComponentClient } from '@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs'
        import { cookies } from 'next/headers'
        
        export default async function DashboardLayout({ children }) {
          const supabase = createServerComponentClient({ cookies })
          const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession()
          
          if (!session) {
            redirect('/pt-br/login')
          }
          
          return children
        }
        ```
        
        ### Loading State
        ```tsx
        // app/[locale]/dashboard/loading.tsx
        export default function Loading() {
          return (
            <div className="flex items-center justify-center h-screen">
              <div className="animate-spin rounded-full h-32 w-32 border-b-2 border-primary" />
            </div>
          )
        }
        ```
        
        ### Error Boundary
        ```tsx
        // app/[locale]/error.tsx
        'use client'
        
        export default function Error({
          error,
          reset,
        }: {
          error: Error & { digest?: string }
          reset: () => void
        }) {
          return (
            <div>
              <h2>Something went wrong!</h2>
              <button onClick={reset}>Try again</button>
            </div>
          )
        }
        ```
        
        ## API Integration
        - Use fetch with proper error handling
        - Implement retry logic for failed requests
        - Show loading states during API calls
        - Cache responses when appropriate
        - Handle network errors gracefully
        
        Example:
        ```tsx
        const API_URL = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:8000'
        
        async function fetchResumes() {
          try {
            const response = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/resumes`, {
              headers: {
                'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`
              }
            })
            
            if (!response.ok) {
              throw new Error('Failed to fetch resumes')
            }
            
            return await response.json()
          } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error fetching resumes:', error)
            throw error
          }
        }
        ```
        
        ## SEO Best Practices
        - Use Next.js Metadata API
        - Implement proper Open Graph tags
        - Add structured data (JSON-LD)
        - Create sitemap.xml
        - Implement proper robots.txt
        - Use canonical URLs
        
        Example:
        ```tsx
        // app/[locale]/page.tsx
        import { Metadata } from 'next'
        
        export const metadata: Metadata = {
          title: 'CV Match - AI Resume Optimizer',
          description: 'Optimize your resume with AI',
          openGraph: {
            title: 'CV Match',
            description: 'AI-powered resume optimization',
            images: ['/og-image.png'],
          },
        }
        ```
        
        ## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
        - ‚ùå Don't use 'use client' everywhere (keep Server Components)
        - ‚ùå Don't hardcode text strings (use next-intl)
        - ‚ùå Don't forget loading and error states
        - ‚ùå Don't skip accessibility features
        - ‚ùå Don't use inline styles (use Tailwind)
        - ‚ùå Don't create custom components if Shadcn has them
        - ‚ùå Don't forget to test both pt-br and en
        - ‚ùå Don't expose API keys in client code
        - ‚ùå Don't skip TypeScript types
        - ‚ùå Don't forget mobile responsiveness
        
        ## JSON File Editing
        - Package.json: Dependencies, scripts
        - Tsconfig.json: TypeScript configuration
        - Messages/*.json: Translation files (pt-br.json, en.json)
        - Tailwind.config.js: Tailwind configuration (converted to JSON)
        - .eslintrc.json: ESLint rules
        - Component.json: Shadcn/ui configuration
